Rule Name: design-system.mdc
Description: Design System Structure in Parsa App (Material Design 3)

# Theme Configuration
The app uses Material Design 3 but has its theme configuration spread across multiple files:

## Core Theme Definition
@lib/core/presentation/theme.dart
- Main theme configuration using `getThemeData()`
- Takes `lightColorScheme` and `accentColor` as parameters
- Sets up Material 3 with custom font 'Nunito'
- Configures input, FAB, bottom sheet, and list tile themes

## Custom Colors Extension
@lib/core/presentation/app_colors.dart
- Defines `AppColors` extending `ThemeExtension`
- Contains brand color constants:
  - `brandBlue = Color(0xFF1c64f2)`
  - `brandDarkblue = Color(0xFF1724c9)`
  - `brandLightBlue = Color(0xFF30a8ff)`
- Manages custom color palette including:
  - danger/success colors
  - brand colors
  - input fills
  - surface colors
  - modal backgrounds

## Theme Service
@lib/core/presentation/theme_service.dart
- Provides theme state management
- Allows dynamic theme updates

## Color Picker Options
@lib/core/presentation/widgets/color_picker/color_picker.dart
- Defines `defaultColorPickerOptions` array with material color codes
- Used for accent color selection (currently hardcoded)

# Important Note
The accent color functionality appears to be hardcoded in the theme configuration. The primary color being used is blue (Color(0xFF0F3375)) as defined in app_colors.dart.

# Usage Guidelines
1. Theme access: Use `Theme.of(context)` to access theme data
2. Custom colors: Access via `AppColors.of(context)`
3. Brightness check: Use utility functions:
   - `isAppInDarkBrightness(context)`
   - `isAppInLightBrightness(context)`